英国广播公司对处理罗素品牌不当行为投诉道歉https://www.nme.com/news/tv/tv/bbc-apologises-overhandling-of-russell-brand-brand-misconduct-complaints-3833222?utm_source = rsss间Russell Brand-Misconduct-CompartsVictoria Luxford Thu, 30 Jan 2025 16:15:59 +0000 NewsTV NewsBBC https://www.nme.com/?p=3833222 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="罗素·布兰德（Russell Brand）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>主持人否认了2023年的指控</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/bbc-apologises-over-handling-of-russell-brand-misconduct-complaints-3833222">英国广播公司（BBC）邮政对Russell Brand不当行为投诉的处理道歉，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="罗素·布兰德（Russell Brand）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Photo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/bbc">英国广播公司（BBC）</a>向员工道歉，那些在2006年至2008年之间在2006年至2008年期间为6次音乐和第2台电台工作的报告结束了他的时间后，他对前主持人<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/russell-brand?before=YXJyYXljb25uZWN0aW9uOjM1MDI3NDc=">罗素·布兰德（Russell Brand）</a>所指控的不当行为表示歉意。</p><p> 2023年9月，在<em>第4频道，《泰晤士报》</em>和<em>《星期日泰晤士报》</em>进行调查后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/russell-brand-accused-of-rape-sexual-assault-and-emotional-abuse-3498938">，电视人物被指控强奸，性侵犯和情绪虐待</a>。这四个指控与他的专业和个人生活有关，并与报告中提到的投诉分开。那个月晚些时候，<a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-66882644" target="_blank" rel="noopener">他被指控在洛杉矶录制了2008年的BBC广播节目时，在洛杉矶录制了一名妇女</a>。</p><p> Brand has denied all allegations, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/russell-brand-posts-video-denying-unspecified-serious-criminal-allegations-3498867">releasing a video stating:</a> “Amidst this litany of astonishing, rather baroque attacks are some very serious allegations that I absolutely refute”.</p><p> On page 10 of the 15-page report, led by Peter Johnston, it was stated: “What is clear is that many BBC staff and freelancers, especially in more junior roles, found Russell Brand demanding and difficult to work with and his behaviour extreme, but all felt that there was no point in complaining as they believed they would not be listened to and, rightly or wrongly, that Russell Brand as a high-profile presenter had the support of the station management”. </p><figure id="attachment_3833225" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3833225" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3833225" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention.jpg" alt="罗素·布兰德（Russell Brand）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Russell-Brand-Convention-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3833225" class="wp-caption-text"> Russell Brand pictured last year at the Republican National Convention (credit: Leon Neal/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> Today (January 30), a BBC press release in response to the report read: “When allegations were raised about Russell Brand in 2023, relating to his work at the BBC, it was important that this was looked into methodically. This work has been conducted with the greatest care. We want to thank the individuals who have participated, as we know that it has not been easy to speak out about some of the issues the review addresses”.</p><p> It continued: “The review considered eight complaints of misconduct about Russell Brand, only two of which were made while he was engaged by the BBC, one formally and one informally. It is of great concern that some of these individuals felt unable to raise concerns about Russell Brand&#39;s behaviour at the time, and the BBC has apologised to them as part of this review”.</p><p> “It is also clear that there were compliance inadequacies on some of Russell Brand&#39;s Radio 2 shows which led to content being aired that would not be broadcast today. Russell Brand left the BBC in 2008 following a high-profile editorial breach”.</p><p> The statement concluded by saying: “As has been reported, there is an ongoing police investigation into Russell Brand. The BBC has been in contact with the Metropolitan police throughout the review and they have seen the report. The BBC acknowledges that Russell Brand categorically denies all public allegations made against him”. </p><figure id="attachment_3833233" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3833233" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3833233" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters.jpg" alt="罗素·布兰德（Russell Brand）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/BBC-Headquarters-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3833233" class="wp-caption-text"> (Credit: Peter Dazeley/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> In a separate statement, Culture Secretary Lisa Nandy said: “The complaints against Russell Brand set out in this report are horrendous. As is the fact that staff felt unable to raise concerns because they did not think that they would be believed or taken seriously”.</p><p> “我赞扬那些勇敢地挺身而出分享他们令人震惊的经历的人。 The BBC must now reflect on the conclusions and take action to reassure its staff and the wider public that it takes these issues seriously”.</p><p> “For too long, there has been a culture of silence in the media industry where inappropriate behaviour like Brand&#39;s has been tolerated or downplayed. Power imbalances and a perception that certain stars cannot be challenged are sadly not unique to this case. The BBC, and the wider industry, must now urgently consider what more they can do to make sure that abuse and harassment by anyone, no matter who they are, is not tolerated in any of their workplaces”.</p><p> <em>NME has reached out to Russell Brand&#39;s representatives for comment.</em></p><p> A separate investigation conducted last year by the production company Banijay UK found <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/russell-brand-concerns-not-adequately-addressed-by-channel-4-investigation-finds-3765792">concerns about his behaviour while working for Channel 4 were “not adequately addressed”.</a></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/bbc-apologises-over-handling-of-russell-brand-misconduct-complaints-3833222">BBC apologises over handling of Russell Brand misconduct complaints</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
